args:
Numerous writhing forms of Hastur appear
before the party. They are the ruined remains of
villagers who sought immortality, and the sight
of them makes the party decide to flee the
village. But this choice comes too late, as they
are surrounded by Hastur's innumerable spawn.
They appear to be in pain.
Okay, and now they're...fighting each\nother? Maybe? This is REALLY weird.
It's the old man from this afternoon!\nThe one who wanted Hastur's blessing!
Easy, old timer. Tell us what's wrong.
I was...supposed to receive...\nHis blessing... I DID receive it...
The old man turned into Hastur!
Is that the true nature of his ＂blessing＂?
I don't believe he's attacking so much as\nraging indiscriminately. ...Of course,\nthat's still something of a problem.
This place is getting a little too dangerous\nfor my liking.
Some kind of roar? Or howl?\nBut where—and who—is it from?
Looks like they all decided to split.
They are now servants of Hastur.\nSacrifices burdened by a fate from\nwhich they can never escape.
Did I not warn you not to venture out\nin the darkness of the eventide?
I thought it less of a warning and more\nof a veiled invitation. Was I mistaken?
Who can say? Just know that I truly do not\nwish any harm to fall upon you.
Thrilled to hear it, but we're also not cute\nlittle kids who need mama's protection.
Now tell us what's going on with\nall of the villagers!
That old man who got Hastur's blessing\ntransformed INTO him!
They are now the miserable remains\nof those who sought eternity.
So that is the kernel of truth behind the\nlegend of immortality in this place, mmm?
THAT'S immortality? Being transformed\ninto...into a THING?
This village is ensnared by Hastur himself.\nThose who seek eternity have no choice\nbut to become slave to His yellow cloth.
And why is this Hastur fellow doing this?\nDon't try to tell me its out of love and\nbenevolence.
There is a gate. A great gate meant to\nusher in someone beloved.
Uh, wanna run that by me again?
However, supposing that gate were under\nlock and key, what would you do?
Are you saying that Hastur himself is\nsearching for the key to this gate?
And that he wants this key badly enough\nthat he is willing to sweep up as many\npeople as necessary to find it?
What I can say is that there are none\nin this village save prisoners.
Eternity. Worship. Desire. Obsession.\nAll are slaves to one thing or another.
And yet, I pray that you are not.
Or have you already been so ensnared?
I get that I'M not following any of this,\nbut you also look confused, Heinwald.\n...This worries me.
I have a terribly bad feeling about this.\nI think it would be best for us to leave\nthis village as quickly as possible.
Well, THIS is unusual. I figured you'd\nfight tooth and nail to stay in a place\nas mysterious as this.
I assure you, I am deeply intrigued by all\nof this—but I also have no desire to fall\nvictim to whatever preys on this village.
Fair enough. We'll head out at sunrise.
I don't know, but...I'm afraid!\nSomething...comes! Noooo!
The key is discovered...\nThe silver key to the Ancient Gate...\nMy release is at hand!
